samples.input: Who created the R programming language?

messages.content: Who created the R programming language?

content.text: R was created by Ross Ihaka and Robert Gentleman at the University of Auckland, New Zealand in the early 1990s. The language was named "R" after the first letter of both founders' first names. R was developed as an implementation of the S programming language with lexical scoping semantics inspired by Scheme. It was officially released as an open-source project in 1995 and is now maintained by the R Core Team.
